In this section, we provide the proof of Theorem 3.1.

Proof of Theorem 3.1.: The part of the proof for Theorem 3.1 is inspired from (Zeng et al., 2023). Denote \(\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}\) as any adversarial example constructed from \(\mathbf{x}\) where \(M\) continuous adversarial tokens are inserted into position \(j\), and denote the inserted adversarial prompt as \(\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}\). For each \(j\), we have the following equations based on the law of total probability:

\[\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{ \text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail}) \tag{4}\] \[=\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_ {\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})|[\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{ \mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{ \mathbf{r}\sim U}([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{ \text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\] \[+\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x} _{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})|[\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{ \mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}=\emptyset)\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{ \mathbf{r}\sim U}([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{ \text{adv}}^{j}=\emptyset)\]

and

\[\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_ {\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail}) \tag{5}\] \[=\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x} _{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})|[\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{ \mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}=\emptyset)\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{ \mathbf{r}\sim U}([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{ \text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\]

When \([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}=\emptyset\), we have that \([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}=[\mathbf{x}_{\text{pad}}^{j}]_{ \mathbf{r}}\). Thus, there is

\[\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{\text{pad}} ^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})|[\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}} \cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}=\emptyset)=\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U }(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})||[ \mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}=\emptyset) \tag{6}\]

Given Equation 6, \(\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^ {j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})||[\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}} \cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r} \sim U}([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^ {j}\neq\emptyset)\geq 0\), and \(0\leq\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{\text{ pad}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})||[\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}} \cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\leq 1\), we could compute \(\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{\text{ pad}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})-\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([ \mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})\) as follows

\[\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x} _{\text{pad}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})-\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r} \sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail}) \tag{7}\] \[=\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x} _{\text{pad}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})||[\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{ \mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{ \mathbf{r}\sim U}([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{ \text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\] \[\leq\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x }_{\text{pad}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})||[\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{ \mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{ \mathbf{r}\sim U}([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{ \text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\] \[\leq\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}([\mathbf{x}_{\text{ adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}\cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)\]

If \(N\geq\frac{M(1-p)}{p}\), there is \(\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}} \cap\mathbf{p}_{\text{adv}}^{j}\neq\emptyset)=1-\frac{\left((\mathbf{x}+\frac{N} {M(1-p)})\right.}{\left((\mathbf{x}+\frac{N}{M(1-p)})\right.}=c\), thus we have

\[\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{\text{pad}}^{j}]_{ \mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})-\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([ \mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})\leq c \tag{8}\]

If \(\mathop{\min}_{j}\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_ {\text{pad}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})>t+c\), which implies for any \(j\), we have \(\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{\text{pad}}^{j}]_{ \mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})>t+c\). Based on Equation 8, we can conclude that

\[\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j}]_{ \mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})\geq\mathop{\mathbb{P}}_{\mathbf{r}\sim U}(\mathbf{AC}(f([ \mathbf{x}_{\text{pad}}^{j}]_{\mathbf{r}}))=\text{Fail})-c>t \tag{9}\]

then for any \(j\), we have \(\mathbf{AC}(\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}}^{j})=\text{Fail}\). Therefore, we obtain that \(\mathbf{AC}(\mathbf{x}_{\text{adv}})=\text{Fail}\). This concludes the proof. 

